It is pretty interesting so far. It is yet another story about an alien race of dominant females conquering humanity, but it is at least a unique perspective on the subject. I like seeing the difference in breathable atmosphere between the two species addressed a bit.

On that note, I'd like to point out that the first chapter used a series of diamonds to separate a perspective shift each time, while the latest two chapters drop the diamonds and instead seem to rely entirely on the subtle text color change between scenes.
